  ** electronic configuration:
  the arangemeno of electrons at various shells in atomic configuartion is known as shells:
  valence shell: it is outemost shell:
  valance electron: the electron preseent in the outermost shell or known as valence electron:

  ** octet rule:
   if there is 8 electron in outermost shell of an atom then they are stable and balance and less reactive:
   eg: neon 2, 8
   argon: 2, 8 ,8:
   so here every element want to achive this octet of 8 and want to bet stable :

   valency: the number of electron obtained, donated, or shared to complete the valency or octet of 8 is known as valency:
   when atom loose or form ions they formed charged ions:
   if its donate the elctron then it will be +ve and if it will take electron then negative:

